## 5. Algorithms

### Q: What are the four algorithms and how do they compare?

| Algorithm | Memory | Accuracy | Handles bursts? | Notes |
|-----------|--------|----------|-----------------|-------|
| Fixed Window | Tiny (1 int) | Bad | No | **Boundary burst**: 100 requests at 12:00:59 + 100 at 12:01:00 = 200 in 2 sec |
| Sliding Window Log | Huge (N/user) | Perfect | Yes | Memory explodes at scale |
| Sliding Window Counter | Tiny (2 ints) | Good approx | Yes | Weighted math over previous + current window |
| **Token Bucket** ✅ | Tiny (2 fields) | Great | Yes | Chosen by Stripe. Bucket size = burst; refill rate = sustained rate |

### Q: Why Token Bucket?

Two intuitive knobs (bucket size, refill rate). Naturally handles bursty API traffic. Tiny per-user memory.

