## 9. Scaling to 1M RPS

### Q: What's the bottleneck?

One Redis instance = ~100k-200k ops/sec. Each rate check = 1 op minimum. So one Redis caps at ~100k rate checks/sec, 10× short of our 1M rps target.

### Q: How do we shard?

**Consistent hashing on the client ID.** Each client's state must always land on the same shard, or the algorithm breaks.

```
hash("alice") % 10 → shard 3   (always)
hash("bob")   % 10 → shard 7   (always)
```

10 shards × ~100k ops/sec = 1M rps.

### Q: How is this implemented in practice?

**Redis Cluster** — auto-distributes across 16,384 hash slots. No custom hashing in gateway code; just connect.

