## 10. High Availability

### Q: Fail open or fail closed when Redis dies?

| Mode | Behavior | When to use |
|------|----------|-------------|
| Fail open | Allow all requests | Availability > protection |
| **Fail closed** ✅ | Reject all requests | Protection > availability (our choice) |

Why closed for social media: rate limiter failures often coincide with traffic spikes (that's what caused them). Fail open during a viral event = flood hits DBs = full outage.

### Q: How do we prevent Redis failures?

Master-replica replication per shard. Redis Cluster auto-detects master failure and promotes a replica. Trade-off: replication lag (fine for eventual consistency) + doubled infra cost.

