## 14. Real-World Setup

### Q: Do we actually write rate limiter code?

Usually no. 99% of companies use off-the-shelf gateways (Kong, Envoy, AWS API Gateway) with built-in rate limiting plugins.

### Q: What do we configure vs write?

| What | Language | Who |
|------|----------|-----|
| Gateway config (rules, plugins) | YAML/JSON | Platform team |
| Custom business rules | Lua (Kong) / Go microservice (Envoy RLS) | Backend team |
| Actual limit values | Admin UI | Product/Ops |

Real setup:

```
Cloudflare (DDoS shield)
   ↓
Envoy API Gateway (rate limit plugin)
   ↓ complex rules
Rate Limit Service (custom Go microservice)
   ↓
Redis Cluster (10 shards, master-replica)
```

You write ~50 lines of YAML, not 5000 lines of algorithm code.

